{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  MISC facets snippet — fork of Trade's snippets/facets.liquid.

  Forked: 2026-05-28
  Source: Trade theme, snippets/facets.liquid

  Why forked:
    Trade's facets snippet is 937 lines covering horizontal /
    vertical / drawer / mobile layouts. Our catalog only uses
    the desktop vertical layout, and we need exact control of
    the markup to match the MISC mockup at
    /Cowork/30 Projects/Misc/Mockups/misc-sidebar-mockup.html.

  What we keep from Trade:
    - The <facet-filters-form> custom element + <form id="FacetFiltersForm">
      wrapper so Trade's facets.js can intercept change events
      and run its AJAX refresh against the section.
    - Input names (filter.v.*, filter.p.*) so the URL params
      match Shopify's expected filter format.
    - filter.values / value.active / value.url_to_add /
      value.url_to_remove / value.param_name from the Liquid
      results object.
    - The mobile/drawer layout is not rendered here; Trade's
      original facets snippet stays available for the mobile
      surface if we ever want it (it's never called by our
      catalog section though, so this is just defence).

  Inputs (mirrors Trade's facets snippet):
    - results               : collection or search results
    - enable_filtering
    - enable_sorting
    - filter_type           : 'vertical' (we only handle vertical)
    - paginate

  Re-merge with Trade upstream:
    When Trade ships a major update, skim facets.liquid for new
    Liquid patterns (new filter types, new metadata on values,
    accessibility tweaks) and port them here. The original
    facets.liquid stays untouched.
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  if results.url
    assign results_url = results.url
  else
    assign sort_by = results.sort_by | default: results.default_sort_by
    assign terms = results.terms | escape
    assign results_url = '?q=' | append: terms | append: '&options%5Bprefix%5D=last&sort_by=' | append: sort_by
  endif

  assign show_more_threshold = 8
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  MISC: no Trade `small-hide` here. Our filter sidebar IS the mobile
  drawer (the whole .facets-wrapper slides in on <1024px), so the
  facet form must stay visible on phones too. Trade's `small-hide`
  set display:none below 749px, which left the drawer body empty.
{%- endcomment -%}
<facet-filters-form class="facets misc-sidebar" data-id="{{ section.id }}">
  <form
    id="FacetFiltersForm"
    class="misc-sidebar__form"
  >
    {%- if results.terms -%}
      <input type="hidden" name="q" value="{{ results.terms | escape }}">
      <input name="options[prefix]" type="hidden" value="last">
    {%- endif -%}

    <div id="FacetsWrapperDesktop">
      {%- comment -%}
        Empty wrapper kept for facets.js DOM hooks. The real
        filter UI follows below. Active-facets + FILTER heading
        live in the misc-filter-bar above the catalog body, not
        inside the sidebar.
      {%- endcomment -%}

      {%- for filter in results.filters -%}
        <details class="misc-filter-group js-filter" open data-index="{{ forloop.index }}">
          <summary class="misc-filter-group__summary">
            <span class="misc-filter-group__title">{{ filter.label | escape }}</span>
            {%- if filter.type == 'price_range' -%}
              {%- if filter.min_value.value != blank or filter.max_value.value != blank -%}
                <span class="misc-filter-group__badge">1</span>
              {%- endif -%}
            {%- elsif filter.active_values.size > 0 -%}
              <span class="misc-filter-group__badge">{{ filter.active_values.size }}</span>
            {%- endif -%}
          </summary>

          {%- case filter.type -%}

            {%- when 'price_range' -%}
              <div class="misc-filter-group__body">
                <div class="misc-price-inputs">
                  <label class="misc-price-input-wrap">
                    <span class="misc-price-input-prefix">{{ cart.currency.symbol }}</span>
                    <input
                      type="number"
                      name="{{ filter.min_value.param_name }}"
                      value="{{ filter.min_value.value | money_without_currency | replace: ',', '.' }}"
                      placeholder="Min"
                      class="misc-price-input"
                      aria-label="Minimum price"
                      min="0"
                      step="0.01"
                    >
                  </label>
                  <label class="misc-price-input-wrap">
                    <span class="misc-price-input-prefix">{{ cart.currency.symbol }}</span>
                    <input
                      type="number"
                      name="{{ filter.max_value.param_name }}"
                      value="{{ filter.max_value.value | money_without_currency | replace: ',', '.' }}"
                      placeholder="Max"
                      class="misc-price-input"
                      aria-label="Maximum price"
                      min="0"
                      step="0.01"
                    >
                  </label>
                </div>
                {%- comment -%}
                  Range hint shows both ends per the mockup
                  ("Range €1.50 to €245.00"). filter.range_min is
                  Shopify's lower bound for the collection; falls
                  back to 0 if the filter object doesn't expose it.
                  MISC: changed from "Range up to X" to two-ended.
                {%- endcomment -%}
                <p class="misc-filter-group__hint">
                  Range {{ filter.range_min | default: 0 | money }} to {{ filter.range_max | money }}
                </p>
              </div>

            {%- when 'boolean', 'list' -%}
              <ul class="misc-filter-group__options" role="list">
                {%- for value in filter.values -%}
                  {%- assign show_class = '' -%}
                  {%- if forloop.index > show_more_threshold and value.active == false -%}
                    {%- assign show_class = ' misc-filter-option--hidden' -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                  <li class="misc-filter-option-row{{ show_class }}">
                    <label class="misc-filter-option">
                      <input
                        type="checkbox"
                        class="misc-filter-option__check"
                        name="{{ value.param_name }}"
                        value="{{ value.value | escape }}"
                        {% if value.active %}checked{% endif %}
                        {% if value.count == 0 and value.active == false %}disabled{% endif %}
                      >
                      <span class="misc-filter-option__label">{{ value.label | escape }}</span>
                      <span class="misc-filter-option__count">{{ value.count }}</span>
                    </label>
                  </li>
                {%- endfor -%}
              </ul>
              {%- if filter.values.size > show_more_threshold -%}
                {%- assign hidden_count = filter.values.size | minus: show_more_threshold -%}
                <button
                  type="button"
                  class="misc-filter-more"
                  data-misc-show-more
                  aria-expanded="false"
                >
                  Show {{ hidden_count }} more
                </button>
              {%- endif -%}

          {%- endcase -%}
        </details>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      No-JS submit fallback: when JS is off the buyer needs a
      button to apply the filters. With JS on, Trade's facets.js
      intercepts input changes and AJAX-refreshes the page.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <noscript>
      <div class="misc-sidebar__noscript">
        <button type="submit" class="misc-sidebar__submit">Apply filters</button>
      </div>
    </noscript>

  </form>
</facet-filters-form>
